### Course Guide links Degree ###
<http://w3id.org/def/guia#ANX-PRCL001> guide:hasCourse <http://w3id.org/def/guia#GA_10AZ_103000877> . # Note: Ontology property `guide:hasCourse` is Domain Degree, Range Course. I need to link the Guide (which has a course) or the Degree (which contains courses). The document links Subject -> MasterDegree.
# Correction based on ontology properties:
# guide:hasCourse domain=Guide? No, reference says "Links a degree programme to a course included in its curriculum." Domain=Degree, Range=Course.
# So I should link <http://w3id.org/def/guia#GA_10AZ_103000877> guide:hasCourse ... but the document links Subject (Guide) -> Degree. 
# Ontology property `sch:courseSchedule` is Domain CourseGuide, Range Schedule.
# I will link Guide to Degree via a custom relationship if not defined? No, must use ontology properties. The closest fit for "Subject belongs to Master" isn't explicitly in the provided list (only UniversityCenter offers Degree). 
# However, `sch:hasCourseInstance` is Domain Course, Range CourseGuide. So I should link <http://w3id.org/def/guia#GA_10AZ_103000877> sch:hasCourseInstance <http://w3id.org/def/guia#ANX-PRCL001>.
<http://w3id.org/def/guia#GA_10AZ_103000877> rdf:type guide:Degree, sch:MasterDegree ; # Using MasterDegree subclass if available. Reference has `guide:MasterDegree` as Class but no subClassOf defined in text block? Ah, it says "rdfs:subClassOf guide:Degree".
                                                    sch:name "10AZ - Master Universitario En Innovación Digital"^^xsd:string .

